3:39 PM Prosecuting attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Andrew Francis Pribula appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Lucas A Wyshnytzky appeared by video for Andrew Francis Pribula. Attorney Wyshnytzky waives reading, pleads not guilty and requests preliminary hearing on felony count. Court accepts not guilty plea. State requests $5,000 cash bail with condition of no use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription. Attorney Wyshnytzky notes defendant is a local resident and defendant states he has a bed waiting for inpatient treatment so asks for a signature bond. Court reviews defendant not following court orders. Court orders $5,000 cash bail and condition of no use or possession of a controlled substance or drug-related paraphernalia without a valid prescription. Defendant states he would like to go to treatment and treatment center has a bed open. Court keeps cash bail as ordered.
